&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Ceribell&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ceribell is a medical technology company focused on transforming the diagnosis and management of patients with serious neurological conditions. The Ceribell System is a novel, point-of-care electroencephalography (“EEG”) platform specifically designed to address the unmet needs of patients in the acute care setting, and is being used in hundreds of community hospitals, large academic facilities and major IDN&#39;s across the country. Our entire team is driven by a shared commitment to transforming the landscape of critical care through our rapid seizure detection technology, come join the movement!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ceribell is looking for a Clinical Researcher to oversee our open projects focused on data acquisition and investigator-initiated studies (IIS) at our partner institutions. This is a unique opportunity for a motivated individual to apply their advanced EEG research skills and project management expertise in a fast-paced industry setting. You will be the central point of contact for our research partnerships, ensuring the scientific integrity, smooth execution, and successful completion of critical projects that drive our product and clinical evidence development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data Acquisition and Investigator-Initiated Studies: Guide studies from proposal to publication. This includes interacting with principal investigators (PIs), clinical teams, contracts, and operations to get studies launched. Once live, you will actively manage ongoing studies by tracking data integrity, monitoring publication progress, and ensuring alignment with research objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Internal Data Curation: Manage the flow of external EEG and clinical data from our partner sites. You&#39;ll be responsible for monitoring data submissions, performing initial quality checks, cleaning the data, and preparing it for algorithm development. This involves meticulous data cleaning, quality assurance, and transforming complex clinical information into a machine-readable format to support our R&amp;amp;D efforts. You&#39;ll also troubleshoot any issues with partner sites to ensure a consistent and scientifically reliable data source.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data Analysis and Publication: You will perform preliminary data analyses, generate scientific insights, and contribute to or lead publications based on the findings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Brain Data: Demonstrated experience working with brain-derived data, like EEG or neuroimaging, in a research or clinical setting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medical Research Background: A strong understanding of the medical research process, including study design, data collection, and scientific publication. Experience managing clinical research projects from inception to launch, execution and completion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data Management Skills: Proficiency in data cleaning and curation, with an eye for detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project Management Skills: Ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously in a fast-paced environment where priorities can shift quickly and to solve problems proactively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communication: Excellent written and verbal communication skills as well as ability to communicate effectively with diverse stakeholders. Proven ability to build and maintain relationships with internal teams and external partners.&lt;/li&gt;
